Law firm Webber Wentzel, on behalf of the Helen Suzman Foundation, Section27 and Save South Africa, issued Bell Pottinger with a letter on Tuesday that requested certain pieces of information &#8220;as a matter of urgency&#8221;.This comes after the local advocacy groups launched a joint probe into the UK PR firm&#8217;s conduct in South Africa. The findings of which will be used to form recommendations to the relevant UK regulatory bodies.These recommendations &#8220;aim to assist the UK regulatory bodies in understanding the social, economic and potential legal implications of Bell Pottinger&#8217;s conduct,&#8221; the letter reads.The letter refers to the intention of the public interest organisations, which is to &#8220;protect the South African constitution&#8221;. A copy of the letter to can be found here.